          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-900 mb-4">
              Safety & Compliance
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Incorrect installation can compromise fire door performance and
              fail to meet Building Regulations and fire safety standards,
              putting occupants at risk.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-900 mb-4">
              Performance Assurance
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Professional installation ensures fire doors function correctly
              during emergencies, providing the intended fire resistance and
              smoke protection.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-900 mb-4">
              Warranty Protection
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Manufacturer warranties often require professional installation.
              DIY or unqualified installation can void warranty coverage.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-900 mb-4">
              Long-term Reliability
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Proper installation extends fire door lifespan and reduces
              maintenance costs while ensuring continued compliance and safety.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

